=== Item abilities ===
Item abilities allow [[Items|items]] to have special "abilities" within worlds, such as movement speed changes. These abilities can be disabled by world creators and/or instance moderators.

Client translation strings:

* ''"Prop Abilities"<ref>"Prop Abilities", "Header for prop's list of special abilities shown in the inventory and shop." - [https://crowdin.com/editor/vrchat-application/19/en-zhcn#143410 Crowdin]</ref>''
* ''"Modifies Player Movement"<ref>"Modifies Player Movement", "Shown on items in the inventory and shop that modify how the player moves." - [https://crowdin.com/editor/vrchat-application/19/en-zhcn#143408 Crowdin]</ref>''
* ''"This ability is disabled by the world creator and cannot be enabled."<ref>"This ability is disabled by the world creator and cannot be enabled.", "This ability is disabled by the world creator and cannot be enabled. Instance settings button QM tooltip" - [https://crowdin.com/editor/vrchat-application/19/en-zhcn#143398 Crowdin]</ref>''
Options on the website in world settings:

* ''"Props Enabled/Disabled"''
* ''"Props that Modify Player Movement"''

=== Steam Frame ===

Steam Frame will be supported at release with a native application. A build is already available.<ref> https://steamdb.info/changelist/36482738/</ref>

=== Profile and Nameplate Customization ===

Decorate your Profile with Icons Frames, Profile Effects, Banners. Banners can be customImage (current banners), or color (hex rgb, solid color). As well as Nameplate Effects. Similar to Discords customizability. Decorations can be bought in the [[Shop]].

== Officially mentioned ==

These are features that have been talked about or shared publicly by VRChat staff. They could be worked on, but appear to have no implementation yet.

=== New character controller for worlds ===

A long-running request proposes a replacement world character controller with better moving platform support, smoother stairs and slopes, improved unstuck behavior, collider push interaction, and broader Udon control.<ref name="CannyNewCharacterController">[https://feedback.vrchat.com/udon/p/new-character-controller-for-worlds "New Character Controller for Worlds"] on ''feedback.vrchat.com''; posted April 30, 2024; retrieved March 14, 2026.</ref>

The thread is currently marked ''interested''. A staff update on the post says work is currently halted while other projects are prioritized, with a note that updates will be shared if the item re-enters the roadmap.<ref name="CannyNewCharacterController" />

In March 2026 community discussion, a former VRChat employee allegedly involved with this work claimed they were the only person assigned to it before early-2025 layoffs, and that the feature had been close to shipping.

In April 2026, VRChat employee Sai confirmed on X that the new character controller remains "on the back burner" with no ETA and is not currently being worked on.<ref name="SaiXPost">[https://x.com/Sairenix/status/2042786856899629187 Post] on ''x.com''; posted April 11, 2026; retrieved April 12, 2026.</ref>

=== Age verification rollout ===

VRChat staff have described age verification rollout in stages. In a livestream in March 2026, the team stated there is no public timeline for broad rollout beyond [[VRC+]], while aiming for the most accessible and low-cost path possible.

In December 2025, VRChat stated it is working to reduce the cost of age verification through negotiation, partnership, and optimization, without announcing a price point, and that its long-term goal—finances permitting—is to make verification free for everyone.<ref name="TrustSafety2025Blog">[https://hello.vrchat.com/blog/trust-safety-update-2025 "Safety, Freedom, and the Future of VRChat"] on ''hello.vrchat.com''; dated December 19, 2025; retrieved June 9, 2026.</ref> The same announcement expects [[Age Verification]] to function alongside reintroduced [[Content Gating]] in the first half of 2026.

=== Content gating reintroduction ===

VRChat announced it will reintroduce [[Content Gating]] to limit access to content based on tags, with some content requiring [[Age Verification]] to view.<ref name="TrustSafety2025Blog" /> The change is expected in the first half of 2026.

The stated goal is a baseline expectation of content safety for public instances: public instances and non-verified spaces must be suitable for a general audience. VRChat described this as setting a clear standard for what content is permissible where, and as a tool to reduce exposure to adult or suggestive content in broadly accessible spaces.<ref name="TrustSafety2025Blog" />

=== Group moderation tools ===

VRChat stated it is exploring ways to give [[Groups|group]] owners and moderators stronger tools to enforce community norms and take consistent action against bad actors.<ref name="TrustSafety2025Blog" /> No specific tools or timeline were announced.

=== OSC: Output for Haptics ===

A milestone created in 2022 on the VRChat Community OSC GitHub repository proposes streaming OSC data representing touches or collisions with avatars to interface with haptic devices.<ref name="osc-milestones">[https://github.com/vrchat-community/osc/milestones Milestones] on ''github.com/vrchat-community/osc''; retrieved April 6, 2026.</ref>

=== OSC: Udon ===

A milestone created in 2022 on the VRChat Community OSC GitHub repository plans to enable [[Udon]] to read and write OSC data for use in VRChat worlds.<ref name="osc-milestones" />

=== Render pipeline migration (URP/HDRP) ===

Community discussion periodically suggests migrating VRChat from Unity's Built-in Render Pipeline (BiRP) to URP or HDRP. As of March 2026, no official release announcement or Open Beta plan has been published for a migration of this scope.
Recent staff commentary only indicates long-term internal planning tied to BiRP deprecation, without concrete deliverables or timelines.

=== Platform-wide streamed event ===

On June 22, 2026, VRChat opened a public interest check for performers and venues for a planned large, platform-wide event.<ref name="VRChatMusicInterestBsky">[https://bsky.app/profile/vrchat.com/post/3movpjgim422n "Music Performance Interest"] post on ''bsky.app''; posted June 22, 2026; retrieved June 22, 2026.</ref> According to the application form, the event would be officially promoted across VRChat's social media, video, and in-app discovery, and "broadcast beyond standard instances using streaming tech".<ref name="VRChatEventForm">[https://forms.gle/sgGRLYr6XAqhv5K89 "VRChat Event — Performer & Venue Interest"] application form on ''forms.gle''; retrieved June 22, 2026.</ref>

VRChat stated the timing, format, and whether the event happens are not confirmed. For a first event, performances would likely be about one hour and pre-recorded, in one of two time slots targeting late August or November 2026. The streaming technology was not otherwise detailed.<ref name="VRChatEventForm" />

